div.p:
And whereas it is provided in its Article V that the said Treaty shall be binding
                    on the States ratifying it from the date on which five signatory governments
                    have ratified the same, and shall be enforced for five years;

And whereas, the said Treaty was ratified by the United States of America on
                    January 28, 1905; by Guatemala on April 25, 1902; by El Salvador on May 19,
                    1902; by Peru on October 29, 1903, and by Honduras on July 6, 1904;
